Robert Norton Noyce (December 12, 1927 â€“ June 3, 1990), nicknamed \"the Mayor of Silicon Valley,\" co-founded Fairchild Semiconductor in 1957 and Intel Corporation in 1968. He is also credited (along with Jack Kilby) with the realization of the first integrated circuit or microchip that fueled the personal computer revolution and gave Silicon Valley its name.
